name: ReportMetadata
description: Contains report metadata for a tabular, summary, or matrix report.

getaggregates().name: getAggregates
getaggregates().description: Returns unique identifiers for summary or custom summary formula fields in the report.

getbuckets().name: getBuckets
getbuckets().description: Returns a list of bucket fields in the report.

getcrossfilters().name: getCrossFilters
getcrossfilters().description: Returns information about cross filters applied to a report.

getcurrencycode().name: getCurrencyCode
getcurrencycode().description: Returns report currency, such as USD, EUR, or GBP, for an organization that has multicurrency enabled. The value is null if the organization does not have multicurrency enabled.

getcustomsummaryformula().name: getCustomSummaryFormula
getcustomsummaryformula().description: Returns information about custom summary formulas in a report.

getdescription().name: getDescription
getdescription().description: Returns the description of the report.

getdetailcolumns().name: getDetailColumns
getdetailcolumns().description: Returns unique API names (column names) for the fields that contain detailed data. For example, the method might return the following values: “OPPORTUNITY_NAME, TYPE, LEAD_SOURCE, AMOUNT.”

getdevelopername().name: getDeveloperName
getdevelopername().description: Returns the report API name. For example, the method might return the following value: “Closed_Sales_This_Quarter.”

getdivision(such).name: getDivision
getdivision(such).description: Returns the division specified in the report.

getgroupingsacross().name: getGroupingsAcross
getgroupingsacross().description: Returns column groupings in a report.

getgroupingsdown().name: getGroupingsDown
getgroupingsdown().description: Returns row groupings for a report.

gethasdetailrows().name: getHasDetailRows
gethasdetailrows().description: Indicates whether the report has detail rows.

gethasrecordcount().name: getHasRecordCount
gethasrecordcount().description: Indicates whether the report shows the total number of records.

gethistoricalsnapshotdates().name: getHistoricalSnapshotDates
gethistoricalsnapshotdates().description: Returns a list of historical snapshot dates.

getreportbooleanfilter().name: getReportBooleanFilter
getreportbooleanfilter().description: Returns logic to parse custom field filters. The value is null when filter logic is not specified.

getreportfilters().name: getReportFilters
getreportfilters().description: Returns a list of each custom filter in the report along with the field name, filter operator, and filter value.

getreportformat().name: getReportFormat
getreportformat().description: Returns the format of the report.

getreporttype().name: getReportType
getreporttype().description: Returns the unique API name and display name for the report type.

getscope().name: getScope
getscope().description: Returns the API name for the scope defined for the report. Scope values depend on the report type.

getshowgrandtotal().name: getShowGrandTotal
getshowgrandtotal().description: Indicates whether the report shows the grand total.

getshowsubtotals().name: getShowSubtotals
getshowsubtotals().description: Indicates whether the report shows subtotals, such as column or row totals.

getsortby().name: getSortBy
getsortby().description: Returns the list of columns on which the report is sorted. Currently, you can sort on only one column.

getstandarddatefilter().name: getStandardDateFilter
getstandarddatefilter().description: Returns information about the standard date filter for the report, such as the start date, end date, date range, and date field API name.

getstandardfilters().name: getStandardFilters
getstandardfilters().description: Returns a list of standard filters for the report.

gettoprows().name: getTopRows
gettoprows().description: Returns information about a row limit filter, including the number of rows returned and the sort order.

setaggregates(list).name: setAggregates
setaggregates(list).description: Sets unique identifiers for standard or custom summary formula fields in the report.

setbuckets(list).name: setBuckets
setbuckets(list).description: Creates bucket fields in a report.

setcrossfilters(list).name: setCrossFilters
setcrossfilters(list).description: Applies cross filters to a report.

setcurrencycode(string).name: setCurrencyCode
setcurrencycode(string).description: Sets the currency, such as USD, EUR, or GBP, for report summary fields in an organization that has multicurrency enabled.

setcustomsummaryformula(map,reports.repo.name: setCustomSummaryFormula
setcustomsummaryformula(map,reports.repo.description: Adds a custom summary formula to a report.

setdescription(string).name: setDescription
setdescription(string).description: Sets the description of the report.

setdetailcolumns(list).name: setDetailColumns

setdevelopername(string).name: setDeveloperName
setdevelopername(string).description: Sets the report API name—for example, Closed_Sales_This_Quarter.

setdivision(such).name: setDivision
setdivision(such).description: Sets the division of the report.

setgroupingsacross(list).name: setGroupingsAcross
setgroupingsacross(list).description: Sets column groupings in a report.

setgroupingsdown(list).name: setGroupingsDown
setgroupingsdown(list).description: Sets row groupings for a report.

sethasdetailrows(boolean).name: setHasDetailRows
sethasdetailrows(boolean).description: Specifies whether the report has detail rows.

sethasrecordcount(boolean).name: setHasRecordCount
sethasrecordcount(boolean).description: Specifies whether the report is configured to show the total number of records.

sethistoricalsnapshotdates().name: setHistoricalSnapshotDates
sethistoricalsnapshotdates().description: Sets a list of historical snapshot dates.

setreportbooleanfilter().name: setReportBooleanFilter
setreportbooleanfilter().description: Sets logic to parse custom field filters.

setreportfilters().name: setReportFilters
setreportfilters().description: Sets a list of each custom filter in the report along with the field name, filter operator, and filter value.

setreportformat(reports.reportformat).name: setReportFormat
setreportformat(reports.reportformat).description: Sets the format of the report.

setreporttype(reports.reporttype).name: setReportType
setreporttype(reports.reporttype).description: Sets the unique API name and display name for the report type.

setscope(string).name: setScope
setscope(string).description: Sets the API name for the scope defined for the report. Scope values depend on the report type.

setshowgrandtotal(boolean).name: setShowGrandTotal
setshowgrandtotal(boolean).description: Specifies whether the report shows the grand total.

setshowsubtotals(boolean).name: setShowSubtotals
setshowsubtotals(boolean).description: Specifies whether the report shows subtotals, such as column or row totals.

setsortby(list).description: Sets the list of columns on which the report is sorted. Currently, you can only sort on one column.

setstandarddatefilter(reports.standardda.name: setStandardDateFilter
setstandarddatefilter(reports.standardda.description: Sets the standard date filter—which includes the start date, end date, date range, and date field API name—for the report.

setstandardfilters(list).name: setStandardFilters
setstandardfilters(list).description: Sets one or more standard filters on the report.

settoprows(reports.toprows).name: setTopRows
settoprows(reports.toprows).description: Applies a row limit filter to a report.
